      <section eId="sec_CCRP-215-2">
        <num>CCRP 215.2</num>
        <heading>215.2.  Detaining of persons on premises of correctional institution for questioning about contraband; detention for arrest</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-215-2__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A specifically authorized employee of a correctional institution may use reasonable force to detain a person for questioning on the premises of a correctional institution for a length of time not to exceed one hour, when he has reasonable cause to believe that the person is carrying contraband as defined in R.S. 14:402(D).</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-215-2__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The specifically authorized employee, when he has reasonable cause to believe that the person is carrying contraband as defined in R.S. 14:402(D), may also detain such a person for arrest by a peace officer or for the procurement of a search warrant.  The detention shall not constitute an arrest.
Added by</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112365</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
